A suspect was arrested in Khayelitsha last week for being in possession of abalone. Harare police station spokesperson Capt Siyabulela Vukubi said on Thursday 5 September they received a tip-off about abalone that was stored in a house at C Section. He said on arrival they recovered 936 units of abalone to the value of R327 600. Vukubi said a man (35), who works for the City of Cape Town, was arrested and was due to appear at the Khayelitsha magistrateâ€™s court. He added that further information revealed that the suspect is currently out on bail for a house robbery that occurred in Parow earlier this year.